---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
const CONTACT_EMAIL = 'contact@worldtvchannels.com';
---
<Base
  title="Privacy Policy — World TV Channels"
  description="How we handle data on this site. AdSense, cookies, GDPR."
>
  <article class="container legal">
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="updated">Last updated: 26 May 2026</p>

    <p>
      This policy explains how <strong>World TV Channels</strong> (the website,
      referred to here as “the service”) handles information. We respect your
      privacy and have designed the service to collect as little data as possible.
    </p>

    <h2>1. Who controls the data</h2>
    <p>
      The service is developed and maintained by an independent team (“we”). We
      have no servers for storing user data. For questions about this policy,
      write to <a href={`mailto:${CONTACT_EMAIL}`}>{CONTACT_EMAIL}</a>.
    </p>

    <h2>2. Data the service collects</h2>
    <p>
      <strong>We do not store personal data on our servers.</strong> We do not
      maintain user accounts and do not require registration.
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>Your chosen layout, last-watched channel, favorites and history</strong>
        are saved in your browser’s <em>localStorage</em>. They never leave your
        device and cannot be read by us or other websites.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>A consent cookie</strong> (<code>wtv-consent-v1</code>) is stored
        if you make a choice in the cookie banner, so we don’t ask again. It
        contains no personal data.
      </li>
      <li>
        You can clear all of this data from your browser settings (“Clear site
        data” for this site’s domain).
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>3. Use of the internet</h2>
    <p>The service connects to the internet for the following purposes:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>Streaming TV channels</strong> — video streams come directly from
        the servers of the respective channels. The channel catalogue is obtained
        from the open
        <a href="https://github.com/iptv-org/iptv" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">iptv-org</a>
        project. When you watch a channel, your IP address may be visible to the
        stream’s operator — as with any web streaming.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Advertising</strong> — this site plans to display ads via Google
        AdSense (see the next section).
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Fonts</strong> — the site loads Google Fonts from
        <code>fonts.googleapis.com</code>. Google may see your IP address when
        fonts load.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>4. Advertising (Google AdSense)</h2>
    <p>
      The site plans to use <strong>Google AdSense</strong> to display ads. These
      ad networks and their partners may set cookies and collect information such
      as:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>An advertising identifier for your browser</li>
      <li>IP address, device type, operating system, browser type</li>
      <li>Coarse geolocation (country/city level)</li>
      <li>Interaction with ads (impressions, clicks)</li>
      <li>Pages visited on the site</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      The purpose is to show more relevant ads, measure their effectiveness and
      prevent fraud. This data is processed by Google in accordance with:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <a href="https://policies.google.com/technologies/ads" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
          How Google uses information from sites or apps that use its services
        </a>
      </li>
      <li>
        <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
          Google Privacy Policy
        </a>
      </li>
    </ul>
    <p>Managing personalised ads:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>In your browser: <a href="https://adssettings.google.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Google Ads Settings</a>.</li>
      <li>On the site: you can choose “Necessary only” in the cookie banner.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>5. Cookies on the site</h2>
    <p>The site uses two kinds of cookies and similar technologies:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>Technically necessary</strong> — <code>localStorage</code> entries
        for your chosen layout, favorites, history and cookie choice. Without
        them, the service cannot remember your preferences.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Advertising (third party)</strong> — Google AdSense and its
        partners may set cookies to personalise ads. These are set only after
        your approval in the banner or once AdSense is activated.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>6. Your rights under GDPR</h2>
    <p>As a resident of the European Union you have the right to:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Access your personal data</li>
      <li>Correction or erasure (“the right to be forgotten”)</li>
      <li>Restriction of, or objection to, processing</li>
      <li>Data portability</li>
      <li>Withdraw consent to processing at any time</li>
      <li>Lodge a complaint with a supervisory authority</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      Because we don’t store personal data on our servers, most rights are
      exercised directly from your device — by clearing the site’s data in your
      browser. For questions about data processed by Google AdSense, please
      contact Google via the links above.
    </p>

    <h2>7. Children</h2>
    <p>
      The service is not intended for children under 13, and we do not knowingly
      collect data from children under that age. Adult (NSFW) channels are
      filtered out of the catalogue. If you believe a child has provided us with
      data, please contact us so we can delete it.
    </p>

    <h2>8. Security</h2>
    <p>
      The site is served over HTTPS. Because we don’t hold personal data on a
      server, the main privacy considerations relate to your device and to third
      parties (iptv-org, Google) — we recommend reading their policies too.
    </p>

    <h2>9. Changes to this policy</h2>
    <p>
      We may update this policy from time to time. Significant changes will be
      reflected with a new date at the top of the page.
    </p>

    <h2>10. Contact</h2>
    <p>
      For questions about this policy or your data, please write to:
      <br />
      <a href={`mailto:${CONTACT_EMAIL}`}>{CONTACT_EMAIL}</a>
    </p>
  </article>
</Base>
